SUMMARY
  Once the graph-first selector chooses an axis, the selected graph
  projection canonically splits the cube into 2-point fibers over a
  4-point base. The selected-axis shift/parity pair generates the weak
  su(2) on the fibers. The residual swap of the other two axes acts on
  the base and splits it into 3 ⊕ 1. The joint commutant is therefore
  gl(3) ⊕ gl(1), with compact semisimple part su(3).
  This closes the structural graph-first route to the color lane.

